Description: FOR SALE is a 2014 Fender American FSR Stratocaster in beautiful, 99.9% nearly factory condition. Luscious, creamy Vintage White color. "FSR" stands for Fender Special Run which has some features not included in the normal production of the models. In this case, the pickups are a set of Fender 50s Fat Strats that sound great. The tuners have been upgraded to premium Gotoh locking tuners, and a genuine Fender Mint pickguard has been added to complement the creamy vintage white finish to great effect--the original tortoise shell pickguard comes with it. Comes in a vintage style Fender hardshell case. The tremolo arm has never been used, and comes with the guitar as well. The only thing keeping this beautiful Strat from being 100% is tiny little mark/dent down on the lower side of the body near the output jack--see photo. Other than that there are no scratches, losses, dents, and the frets quite fresh as well. Don't know the weight, my guess is about 7.5 lbs. It's not heavy but not featherweight. See more specs below. This guitar has hardly been touched and it shows. A great one, folks. Thanks for looking! Sorry - due to the rosewood fingerboard, I can only ship within the USA.
